    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="uKiSzw"&gt;After months of waiting, now Android users can take the Arc Search app for a spin. It’s now &lt;a href="https://play.google.com/apps/testing/company.thebrowser.arc"&gt;available as an open beta&lt;/a&gt; on the Google Play Store after developers teased &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/23/24226870/arc-is-coming-to-android-soon"&gt;an Android version&lt;/a&gt; of the app in August.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="PAAht9"&gt;Arc is &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23462235/arc-web-browser-review"&gt;The Browser Company’s take on web browsing&lt;/a&gt;, billing itself as offering better customization options than competitors. The Arc Search app also comes with an AI feature, called “Browse for me,” that searches the web for your query and comes up with a summary based on its sources. &lt;/p&gt;
